			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<u>Software Engineer at MLB.com needed to work on MLB.tv Subscription Services</u></p>
<p>
Major League Baseball Advanced Media (MLB.com), the interactive and mobile division of Major League Baseball, is the developer of several award-winning products, Apps and services. Some of these include: MLB Gameday, MLB.TV, Fantasy Baseball, Beat the Streak, and the #1 sports app and a Hall of Fame inductee for iPhone, iPad and Macworld - MLB At Bat! We are also an industry leader in the development and distribution of live streaming video events over multiple platforms.</p>
<p>
We are looking for a Software Engineer with strong Java and SQL experience to extend our MLB.TV subscription services platform. &nbsp;Behind the scenes we support a vast number of web sites, mobile, tablet and set-top apps via a core set of APIs. &nbsp;Your Java development at MLB Advanced Media will be focused around: Streaming Video and Subscription Services. &nbsp;This hands-on positions provide instant gratification for any developer as the code you develop will be used daily by millions across the globe!</p>
<p>
This permanent positions is located in Chelsea Market, New York, NY.</p>
<p>
<strong>We truly believe we offer a unique opportunity for any technologist:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
The opportunity to work on a bleeding edge technology stack</li>
<li>
The opportunity to work with a &quot;world-class&quot; team of Software Engineers</li>
<li>
The opportunity to work on award-winning and complex apps and systems</li>
<li>
The opportunity to have an influence on the innovation of products used globally by millions</li>
<li>
The opportunity to work in a highly collaborative team environment</li>
<li>
We offer a cool, casual, dynamic, creative and fun multimedia environment in an awesome location</li>
<li>
Amazing benefits including - 100% employer-paid Medical, Dental and Vision and company funded Pension Plan.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Must have experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Must be a very strong hands-on Java Developer with expert knowledge of object-oriented development</li>
<li>
Must be well versed in&nbsp;SQL</li>
<li>
Must have outstanding problem-solving skills</li>
<li>
Must be a self-learner and independent</li>
<li>
Must have excellent written and verbal communication skills</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Nice to have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Service oriented architecture, web services design, SOAP and REST</li>
<li>
Experience with high load, highly scalable and distributed applications</li>
<li>
JMS, messaging and asynchronous processing design</li>
<li>
Experience with Information Security policies such as PCI DSS</li>
<li>
Payments or financial services industry experience a plus</li>
<li>
J2EE, Servlets/JSP, EJB, JUnit, Hibernate, Spring, Struts</li>
<li>
Deep knowledge of key object-oriented design patterns, data structures, algorithms, collections, and garbage collection</li>
<li>
Cloud computing experience</li>
<li>
Experience with Mongo, Cassandra or other&nbsp;NoSql solutions</li>
</ul>
